cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD 

The paper proposes a deep learning approach for linear discriminant analysis, which is a common technique for dimensionality reduction and classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper uses a neural network to learn the discriminant features, which suggests the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also discusses the optimization method used for training the network, which could be relevant to the sub-category cs.SD (Software Engineering).
